NEWCASTLE DISEASE - KUWAIT
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Fri, 19 Sep 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol 10, No 37

Emergency report: Text of a fax received on 14 September 1997 from Dr.
Sultan A.S. Khalaf, Deputy Director General, The Public Authority for
Agriculture Affairs and Fish Resources (PAAF), Safat:
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and post-mortem.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 15 August 1997.
Estimated date of first infection: 11 August 1997.
Location No. of outbreaks
Wafra 1
Description of affected population: intensively reared three-week-old
broilers.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
60,000 5,000 2,000 0 0
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: not clearly known, but suspected
to have originated in a slaughter facility on the farm where chickens from
various sources are handled.
B. Mode of spread: probably via slaughterhouse workers who share the same
accommodation as poultry farm workers.
C. Other epidemiological details: this is the first outbreak observed since
October, 1996.
Control measures during reporting period: vaccination of broilers in the
other three farm houses; implementation of zoosanitary measures; palliative
treatment of the affected flock.
--
